Date:   Wed Jun 3 11:43:43 2026 +0800

    fix: portal Modal to body so it covers bottom nav on iOS
    
    The Modal was rendered inside the scrollable tab container, which has
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch. On iOS WKWebView that container gets
    its own compositing layer, so the bottom nav (zIndex 400, rendered at
    App level outside the scroller) painted on top of the Modal (zIndex 500,
    inside the scroller) even though its zIndex was higher.
    
    Portal the Modal to document.body so it escapes the scroller's layer and
    the zIndex ordering applies globally. Verified on web and iOS.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>

